            },
            {
              "id": "overview-1",
              "type": "text",
              "data": {
                "label": "Overview",
                "heading": "Building a cohesive visual language from the ground up.",
                "body": "The client needed a brand identity that could flex across digital and physical touchpoints while maintaining a strong, recognizable presence. We developed a comprehensive system ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” from logo to color to type ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” grounded in their mission and built for scale."
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "usecase-1",
              "type": "use-case",
              "data": {
                "label": "Challenge",
                "heading": "Fragmented brand, no clear voice.",
                "body": "The existing brand had evolved organically over a decade, resulting in inconsistency across channels. Internal teams were creating off-brand assets and customers couldn't recognize the company across contexts.",
                "image": "https://placehold.co/1200x800/222222/ffffff?text=Challenge"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "usecase-2",
              "type": "use-case",
              "data": {
                "label": "Solution",
                "heading": "A system designed to flex and endure.",
                "body": "We created a modular identity system ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” a primary mark, secondary wordmark, icon set, and a defined color and typography system. Every element was documented in a living brand guide accessible to all teams.",
                "image": "https://placehold.co/1200x800/1a1a1a/ffffff?text=Solution",
                "imagePosition": "left"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "usecase-3",
              "type": "use-case",
              "data": {
                "label": "Outcome",
                "heading": "Consistency across every touchpoint.",
                "body": "Within 6 months of rollout, brand recognition scores increased significantly. Internal adoption of the design system reached 95% and the brand guide became a reference point for new hires.",
                "image": "https://placehold.co/1200x800/2d2d2d/ffffff?text=Outcome"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
